routes.name: Burned Fingers. 55ft.
routes.description: Start about 12ft. R of Chilli Con Corner, Below the first of two grooves. Climb up groove to good ledge. Move L for 2ft. (runner)then diagonally R to a small ledge at base of groove (crux). Continue more easily to top. Belay well back. Protection poor.

routes.name: Cygnus. 55ft.
routes.description: Start about 30ft R of Chilli Con Corner. Ascend L-hand corner of slab for about 12ft. (crux). Traverse L for 4ft. to large jug, straight up wall on good holds. Traverse R below block then R for top. Protection poor.

routes.name: Jack in the Green. 70ft.
routes.description: Start 5ft. L of vegetated groove. Gain the base of obvious diagonal crack. Climb this to a bulge and mantelshelf over this to top (crux).

routes.name: Unshaven Texture. 45ft.
routes.description: Start under the obvious overhanging lip to the left of the face. Begin straight up the face to the lip with difficulty and continue out left to good RP.

routes.name: Left Hand Crack. 45ft.
routes.description: Start by two blocks with two cracks in the wall beside them. Climb L-hand crack to ledge. Move R following easy line to top. Protection poor.

routes.name: Come on 30ft.
routes.description: As above stand on the block, climb the crack then onto the slabby wall climb to the top. 33.b variant 30ft. HS as above stand on the block, climb the crack then cross over onto the wall to your left climb to the top.

routes.name: b variant 30ft.
routes.description: as above stand on the block, climb the crack then cross over onto the wall to your left climb to the top.

routes.name: The Overhang
routes.description: The obvious challenge of the crackline splitting the overhang. This repulsed an earlier attempt to onsight and was climbed on top-rope. H.Fogg, G.Fogg. 29/5/05

routes.name: May Contain Nut Traces
routes.description: On the North-facing overhanging face, this is an innocuous-looking crackline towards the left-hand side. Very strenuous and hard to protect. H.Fogg, G.Fogg 29/5/05

routes.name: Easy Crack
routes.description: Short broken crackline towards right-hand side. G.Fogg, H.Fogg 29/5/05

routes.name: The Chute
routes.description: Under overlap and exit through channel. G.Fogg, H.Fogg 29/5/05
